params._options: The configuration options for the presale.
params._token: The address of the ERC20 token being sold.
params._uniswapV2Router02: The address of the Uniswap V2 compatible router.
params._weth: The address of the Wrapped Ether contract (used for ETH pairs).

returns.presaleAddress: The address of the newly created Presale contract.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._newFeeToken: The new fee token address (address(0) for ETH).

params._newHouseAddress: The new address to receive house fees.
params._newHousePercentage: The new house fee percentage (in BPS, e.g., 100 for 1%).

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawFees().details: ERC20 fees are sent directly to the owner during creation.

createPresale((uint256,uint256,uint256,u.notice: Creates a new Presale contract instance.

setFeeConfiguration(uint256,address).notice: Updates the creation fee configuration. Only callable by the owner.

setHouseConfiguration(uint256,address).notice: Updates the house fee percentage and address. Only callable by the owner.

withdrawFees().notice: Allows the owner to withdraw collected ETH fees from this factory contract.
